            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Updated* -\n\nThe founder really had a good vision while setting up this school and she strives hard to maintain the values and keep going. The ambience and architecture is innovative, railway bogeys serve as classroom for lower classes.\nVery good school with a huge campus and good in arts & culture. It's an excellent school with great staff. Children are taken care of and taught the right values.\n\nApart from the above points, if you are taking admission consider all the points in this review and also talk to parents of children in senior classes if you know any.\n\n1. Children till 5th grade sit on the floor to study. There are no benches provided. This actually is a hygiene issue normally but more serious post Covid. This also creates  an orthopedic problem because not all kids are comfortable sitting on the floor for so wrong, nor are they in the right posture.\nThe school says \"this is because doing  activities on the floor is comfortable\", in that case I guess rest of the schools are completely wrong.\n2. Old-fashioned wide school bags (designs which were used 25 years back) instead of regular backpacks which are better on balance and less damaging for the spine. The school insists on this school branded bag (which is fine,) but then they should change their design to a backpack.\n3. The school also insists on their branded pencil pouch which is low quality and mainly impractical than normal compass boxes.\n4. Use of white canvas shoes which get dirty easily and white(hard to maintain) canvas shoes polish is known to be used for addiction and hence banned in many schools.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
