          },
          "datePublished": "2021-09-29",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "School standard has gone down a lot in recent 3-4 years. Lots of teachers have left. School is giving only substitute teachers (parents, temps, etc) even for higher standards like VII and onwards.\n\nLot of student nepotism - teachers will give more attention, exposure only to a select few students and ignore the rest. School performance in Class10 board exam is on a rapid downward.\n\nMany students also leaving - others who get fooled by school's old reputation and get trapped.\n\nSchool management is pathetic - no responsibilities, declining education standard. School takes credit of student awards/achievements earned solely on personal/parent's efforts - with absolutely no help/guidance from school.\n\nDoesn't deserve such high fees. During COVID times, school has not at all reduced fees.\n\nAVOID this pathetic school - look for some other school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
